[2] India
Date: Wed, 12 Apr 2006 19:57:04 -0400 (EDT)
From: Alfonso Rodriguez, M.D.<ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Ahmedabad Newsline, India. 11 Apr 2006 [edited]
<http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=177561>

While a 6-year-old girl from Padra tested positive for dengue even in
tests conducted by the government on Tuesday, 6 more dengue-positive
cases were detected in the screening exercise undertaken by health
officials in Padra town. The 6-year-old [girl] and the other patients
all reside in the posh locality of Padra, near Padariya Chowk. The
first detection of a dengue case was in Padra town, located barely 30
km from Vadodara. While screening 100-odd homes in the residential
vicinity of the patient, 6 cases of mild dengue were found, said Dr K B Patel.
--
