[3] China (Hong Kong, SAR) ex Thailand
Date: Wed, 12 Apr 2006 19:55:31 -0400 (EDT)
From: Alfonso Rodriguez, M.D.<ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>, and A-Lan Banks,
<A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: News.gov.hk, Hong Kong. 12 Apr 2006 [edited]
<http://www.news.gov.hk/en/category/healthandcommunity/060412/html/060412en05010.htm>

The Centre for Health Protection has confirmed an imported case of
Dengue fever involving a 25-year-old man.
He came down with fever, muscle and joint pain on 29 Mar 2006 after
returning from Thailand and was admitted to Princess Margaret
Hospital 6 days later. He has recovered and has been discharged from hospital.
This is the 8th imported Dengue fever case so far in 2006.
His travel companion, a 25-year-old woman, was confirmed yesterday to
have contracted the disease.
