[4] Paraguay
Date: Tue, 11 Apr 2006 18:58:35 -0400 (EDT)
From: Alfonso J. Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Prensa Latina, Cuba. 11 Apr 2006 [edited]
<http://www.plenglish.com/article.asp?ID=%7BE2C30722-B206-4401-B64C-6D38EB4C6673%7D)&language=EN>

Paraguayan health authorities warned on Tuesday that the dengue
epidemic that is already affecting 215 people may spread to other
regions, due to trips at Easter.
They explained that the disease epicenter is in the capital, the
residents of which [will likely be traveling] to other localities and
this could cause infection through the bites of the _Aedes aegypti_
mosquito, the dengue-transmitting agent.
Health Minister Teresa Leon said other infection sources could
develop in the interior of the country within a few days.
The most probable areas for the spread of infection are Ciudad del
Este, 205 miles East of this capital and southeastern Encarnacion, in
Itapua department, where there is a great influx of people and
overcrowding, she said.
Although health authorities are insisting on implementing preventive
measures, dozens of doctors said the health system uses mainly
curative and [supportive] methods.
